        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 2:26AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 226 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Sharon, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vici and Sharon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
